  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Depth Meter</b> is an <linked>informational accessory</linked> that displays the player's <linked>depth</linked>. It is required to craft the <linked>GPS</linked>, which can then be used to craft the <linked>PDA</linked> and the <linked>Cell Phone</linked>. The Depth Meter is dropped by <linked>Cave Bats</linked>, <linked>Giant Bats</linked>, <linked>Jungle Bats</linked>, <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Spore Bats</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span></span>, and <linked>Ice Bats</linked>, with a chance of <span class=\"chance\"><s>1*</s>1/100 (1%)</span> <span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4 i6\" title=\"Desktop, Console, Mobile and Legacy tModLoader versions\"><b></b><i></i></span> / <span class=\"chance\"><s>0.5*</s>1/200 (0.5%)</span> <span class=\"eico i3 i5\" title=\"Old-gen console and 3DS versions\"><b></b><i></i></span>. On the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console</linked>, <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile</linked>, and <linked>[img:Legacy tModLoader version]</linked><linked> Legacy tModLoader</linked> versions, it also drops from <linked>Salamanders</linked>, <linked>Giant Shellys</linked>, and <linked>Crawdads</linked>, with a chance of <span class=\"chance\"><s>1.25*</s>1/80 (1.25%)</span>. In the <linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked><linked> Old-gen console version</linked>, the Depth Meter may also be crafted.",
    "<ul><li>On the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop version</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console version</linked>, <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile version</linked>, and <linked>[img:Legacy tModLoader version]</linked><linked> Legacy tModLoader version</linked>, depth is measured in feet, with one tile equaling two feet.</li><li>On the <linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked><linked> Old-gen console version</linked>, depth is measured in meters, with two tiles equaling one meter.</li><li>On the <linked>Nintendo 3DS</linked><linked>[img:Nintendo 3DS version]</linked><linked> version</linked>, depth is not measured, and the only benefits the accessory grants are from its modifiers.</li></ul>",
    "Depth is measured relative to the boundary between the <linked>Surface</linked> and <linked>Underground</linked> layers, which has a depth of 0 and is displayed as \"Level\". The display shows the vertical distance to this line and the name of the current layer."
  ],
